text: Arriving at 8:00 AM on December 22, 2024, at Copenhagen Airport (CPH), and with a whole two days ahead of you, you'll explore the city's wonders before your 9:00 PM departure on December 23.

Here's what you need to plan:

Activities & Destinations: List the names, exact times for each activity and destination, along with estimated costs. 
Travel Information: Indicate the travel time between each destination, recommend the best mode of transportation for each segment, and include estimated costs. 
Accommodation Details: Provide the hotel name, location, and estimated cost per night. 
Transportation Recommendations: Suggest the best modes of transportation within the city and between destinations. 
Preparations: Mention any necessary bookings (e.g., tickets, reservations) to make in advance.
SMK - The National Gallery of Denmark

Day 1: December 22, 2024

8:30 AM: Upon arrival at Copenhagen Airport, take a taxi to the city center. The fare should be around €20.

9:00 AM: Check-in at the Nordic Breeze hotel, located at Sankt Peders Stræde 34, 1453 Copenhagen. This hotel costs €100 per night.

10:00 AM: Visit the National Museum of Denmark. The ticket costs €3 per person. Make sure to book your tickets in advance.

1:00 PM: Lunch at a local restaurant. Budget around €15-20 per person.

2:00 PM: Head to Amalienborg Palace. The Changing of the Guard ceremony is a must-see, which starts at 3:00 AM.

4:00 PM: Visit Rosenborg Castle. The entry fee is €8 per person.

6:00 PM: Head to Tivoli Gardens. At the park, you can ride a polar bear, which is the most popular experience in the park.

8:00 PM: Dinner at a restaurant in Tivoli Gardens. Budget around €20-25 per person.

Day 2: December 23, 2024

9:00 AM: Start your day at the Copenhagen Zoo. The entry fee is €10 per person.

12:00 PM: Lunch at a restaurant near the zoo. Budget around €15-20 per person.

1:00 PM: Visit SMK - The National Gallery of Denmark. The entry fee is €7 per person.

3:00 PM: Head to the Round Tower. The entry fee is €3 per person.

4:30 PM: Visit Christiansborg Palace. The entry fee is €10 per person.

6:45 PM: Take a taxi to the airport. The fare should be around €20.

In terms of clothing, Copenhagen has mild temperatures in December around 30°C, so light clothing is recommended. For expenses, it's best to have Euros cash on hand as it's widely accepted in Copenhagen.
